ld head, perhaps), or to a state of the mind. One late 13th-century Nottinghamshire family called <i>Croune</i> is more fully named as <i>Madythecroune</i> ‘mad in the head’.","English: occasionally a habitational name for someone who lived or worked at an inn called The Crown, from Middle English <i>coroune</i>, <i>croun(e)</i> ‘crown’."],"variants":[{"name":"Crone","meanings":["Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Cróin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Crón</i>’, a name from <i>crón</i> ‘swarthy’. Compare   Cronin  .","English: nickname from Middle English <i>cron(e)</i> ‘crane’, Old English <i>cran</i>, <i>cron</i>, probably denoting someone with long legs. Compare   Crane  .","Scottish: shortened form   McCrone  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Crown was born in 1505, in Dutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Thomas Wale in 1520, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1525, in Essex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 20."},"et":{"1505–1525":"1505–1525","1503–1563":"1503–1563","1520–1550":"1520–1550","1525":"1525","1503":"1503","29 NOV 1520":"29. november 1520","1520":"1520","1563":"1563","1550":"1550","1505":"1505","Dutton Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dutton, Basset, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1505–1525":"1505–1525","1503–1563":"1503–1563","1520–1550":"1520–1550","1525":"1525","1503":"1503","29 NOV 1520":"29. marraskuuta 1520","1520":"1520","1563":"1563","1550":"1550","1505":"1505","Dutton Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",